TITLE: Customizing Node-RED Docker Image with Local Resources
DESCRIPTION: This Dockerfile builds upon the base Node-RED Docker image and incorporates local project files. It copies package.json, installs dependencies, and adds custom settings and flow files to the image.
SOURCE: https://github.com/node-red/node-red.github.io/blob/master/docs/getting-started/docker.md#2025-04-09_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: dockerfile
CODE:
```
FROM nodered/node-red

# Copy package.json to the WORKDIR so npm builds all
# of your added nodes modules for Node-RED
WORKDIR /data
COPY package.json /data
RUN npm install --unsafe-perm --no-update-notifier --no-fund --only=production
WORKDIR /usr/src/node-red

# Copy _your_ Node-RED project files into place
# NOTE: This will only work if you DO NOT later mount /data as an external volume.
#       If you need to use an external volume for persistence then
#       copy your settings and flows files to that volume instead.
COPY settings.js /data/settings.js
COPY flows_cred.json /data/flows_cred.json
COPY flows.json /data/flows.json
```

