TITLE: Implementing Asynchronous preRoute Hook in Node-RED
DESCRIPTION: Example of implementing an asynchronous preRoute hook that handles message cloning and performs async operations. This hook is called before a message is routed to its destination.
SOURCE: https://github.com/node-red/node-red.github.io/blob/master/docs/api/hooks/messaging/index.md#2025-04-09_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
RED.hooks.add("preRoute", (sendEvent, done) => {
    // As this hook needs to do async work, clone the message if needed
    if (sendEvent.cloneMessage) {
        sendEvent.msg = RED.util.cloneMessage(sendEvent.msg);
        sendEvent.cloneMessage = false;
    }
    someAsyncAPI(sendEvent).then(() => {
        done()
    }).catch(err => {
        // An error means stop processing this message
        done(err);
    })
});
```

