TITLE: Error Handling in Node-RED Node Input Listener
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates error handling within a Node-RED node's input listener, compatible with both Node-RED 1.0 and earlier versions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/node-red/node-red.github.io/blob/master/docs/creating-nodes/node-js.md#2025-04-09_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let node = this;
this.on('input', function(msg, send, done) {
    // do something with 'msg'

    // If an error is hit, report it to the runtime
    if (err) {
        if (done) {
            // Node-RED 1.0 compatible
            done(err);
        } else {
            // Node-RED 0.x compatible
            node.error(err, msg);
        }
    }
});
```

